3 SENATE BILL NO. 1220 By: Alvord
4
5
6 An Act relating to memorial highway and bridge
designations; designating the Terry Walker Memorial
7 Interchange; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.510 of Title 69, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 The interchange of Interstate 35 and Blue Bell Road in Springer,
15 Carter County, shall be designated as the “Terry Walker Memorial
16 Interchange”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
17 permanent markers bearing that name to be placed at the interchange.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
19 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AERONAUTICS AND TRANSPORTATION
February 9, 2026 - DO PASS
